# Taiga tickets (TJW)

When implementing a Taiga user story in `~/git`:

- Branch: `{feat|fix|docs|chore|refactor|test|task}/TJW-###-short-slug` (infer prefix from ticket text).
- Commit messages must start with `TJW-###:`.
- One PR per modified repository; link all PRs in the Taiga comment when done.
- Prefer the repo explicitly named in the ticket (`~/git/foo`) over multi-repo exploration.
- After implementation, move the card to **Testing** unless the user specifies another column.
- Use the **taiga-ticket** skill for the full fetch → implement → PR → Taiga workflow.
